# .trivyignore

# --- cert-manager (Jetstack upstream manifest, k8s/cert-manager/cert-manager.yaml) ---
# These are cert-manager's required-by-design permissions, not misconfigurations.
# Do not remove these permissions in the manifest itself — cert-manager will break.

# cert-manager needs cluster-scoped Secret access: it stores every issued TLS cert as a Secret
AVD-KSV-0041

# cainjector needs to modify webhook configs to inject CA bundles (core CA injection function)
AVD-KSV-0114

# ACME HTTP-01 challenge solver needs to manage Services/Ingresses to serve challenge responses
AVD-KSV-0056

# cert-manager images are pulled from quay.io (Jetstack's registry) — legitimate, just not
# in Trivy's default trusted-registry allowlist
AVD-KSV-0125

# --- Terraform (modules/vpc/main.tf) ---
# Public IP accepted: ingress restricted to SSH from allowed_ssh_cidr only,
# no NAT gateway budget for this project. Re-evaluate if instance count/exposure grows.
AVD-AWS-0164